 #######################################################################
#                                                                       #
#                                                                       #
#   Add worlds in gazebo without touching environnement variables       #
#                                                                       #
#                                                                       #
 #######################################################################
# 
#  To add easely gazebo worlds without modifying the env variables in the
# shell script : (location <usr/share/gazebo_version/gazebo/setup.sh>)
# 
# Here are the variables:
# 
# GAZEBO_MODEL_PATH: colon-separated set of directories where Gazebo 
# will search for models
# 
# GAZEBO_RESOURCE_PATH: colon-separated set of directories where Gazebo 
# will search for other resources such as world and media files.
# 
# GAZEBO_MASTER_URI: URI of the Gazebo master. This specifies the IP and 
# port where the server will be started and tells the clients 
# where to connect to.
# 
# GAZEBO_PLUGIN_PATH: colon-separated set of directories where Gazebo 
# will search for the plugin shared libraries at runtime.
# 
# GAZEBO_MODEL_DATABASE_URI: URI of the online model database where 
# Gazebo will download models from.
# 
# 
# You can add your world in the <gazebo_location>/worlds directory 
#
# To add a model, add your folder into the model directory 
#
#
#  
# .
# ├── media
# │   ├── audio
# │   ├── dem
# │   ├── fonts
# │   ├── gui
# │   │   ├── fonts
# │   │   ├── imagesets
# │   │   ├── looknfeel
# │   │   └── schemes
# │   ├── materials
# │   │   ├── programs
# │   │   │   └── deferred_rendering
# │   │   │       ├── deferred_lighting
# │   │   │       └── deferred_shading
# │   │   ├── scripts
# │   │   └── textures
# │   ├── models
# │   ├── rtshaderlib
# │   │   └── materials
# │   └── skyx
# ├── models
# │   ├── ground_plane
# │   └── sun
# └── worlds
# 
#

